law.catch_line: Interference with forestry officer or employee.
law.text: No person shall resist, obstruct, interfere with or threaten, or attempt to intimidate, or in any other manner interfere with any officer or employee of the Energy and Environment Cabinet in the discharge of his duties under the provisions of KRS Chapter 149.
law.history: Amended 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 24, sec. 149, effective July 15, 2010. -- Amended 1974 Ky. Acts ch. 74, Art. III, sec. 13(3). -- Created 1966 Ky. Acts ch. 23, sec. 51 (1).
